Azure follows a hierarchical structure:
Management Group → Subscription → Resource Group → Resources

This hierarchy allows policies, access controls, and configurations to be inherited downwards.

# Real-Life Example 1:
For example, if a policy is applied at the management group level, it automatically applies to all subscriptions and resource groups under it.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is enforcing security policies across an organization. For instance, requiring encryption for all storage accounts can be applied at the top level.

# Real-Life Example 2:
Another example is cost management, where budgets can be controlled at subscription or resource group levels.

This hierarchical model ensures consistency, scalability, and easier management of cloud environments.
